# =============================================================================
# EXPLANATION:
# =============================================================================
#
# SECURITY CRITICAL:
# - .env files contain API keys and database passwords
# - NEVER commit these to Git, especially public repos
#
# PYTHON SPECIFIC:
# - __pycache__ and *.pyc are compiled Python files (auto-generated)
# - Virtual environments (venv/) contain installed packages (large, not needed)
#
# DATABASE:
# - Backup files can be huge and contain sensitive data
# - Keep schema.sql (table definitions) but ignore data dumps
#
# LOGS:
# - Can grow very large
# - May contain sensitive information
# - Generated during runtime, not source code
#
# DOCKER:
# - postgres_data/ contains actual database data (huge, auto-generated)
# - docker-compose.override.yml is for local customizations
#
# IDE FILES:
# - Personal preferences, not needed by others
# - Can cause conflicts between team members
#
# =============================================================================
